<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920317-0159</DOCNO><DOCID>920317-0159.</DOCID><HL>   Logicon's U.S. Army Contract</HL><DATE>03/17/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   LGN</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><NS>DEFENSE CONTRACTS (DFC)</NS><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)KANSAS (KS)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   LOS ANGELES -- Logicon Inc. said the U.S. Army exercised a$10 million contract option for the company to providetechnical support for the computer-based Battle CommandTraining Program in Fort Leavenworth, Kan.   The option, the second of four one-year options, bringsthe contract value to date to $24 million. Logicon, aprovider of advanced technology systems and services, willmodify software and provide engineering and other technicalsupport for a series of battle simulations.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>